#history of #scrabble

Scrabble was invented by #jamesbrunot in 1948

It was #jackstraus then #president of #Macys was playing the #boardgame while on #vacation in 1952. Shocked to see his store didn't sell scrabble, he ordered a ton of them so everyone of his #customers  would have a #scrabblegame in their home.

Brunot then sold the game to #selchowandrighter and that year they sold 4,000,000 units.

The #game has since then sold over 150,000,000 units and is in approximately one third of all homes in the states and #Britain

It is currently available in 121 #countries and in 29 #languages 
The #definition of Scrabble means to scratch madly.
